# Project Documentation Rule

- Use `docs/README.md` as the entry point for project context.
- Keep `docs` updated whenever we define or change requirements, plans, decisions, architecture, or notable assets.
- Prefer short, task-focused docs that are easy to scan.
- When starting new work, check the relevant docs first if project context matters.
- Record meaningful decisions in `docs/decision-log.md`.
- Update `docs/product-requirements.md` when scope or behavior changes.
- Update `docs/architecture.md` when structure, stack, or data flow changes.
- Reference supporting assets from docs so they stay discoverable.
